{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ServiceReject message encoding of optional T3442 timer field\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_service_reject()` function was incorrectly encoding the optional T3442 timer field without checking if it was actually present using the presencemask field. This caused issues when the timer should not be included in the message.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/ServiceReject.h`: Added presence mask constant and IEI definition for T3442 timer\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/ServiceReject.c`: Fixed encoding function to check presence mask before encoding optional field and updated decoding function to properly handle optional fields\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `encode_service_reject()` with a service reject message that does not include the T3442 timer (presencemask not set), the function would still attempt to encode the timer field, resulting in incorrect message formatting and potential buffer overflows. The message would contain garbage data for the timer field instead of omitting it entirely.\n\n"
}